Package uk.ac.manchester.cs.spinnaker.rest.utils

Class RestClientUtils

java.lang.Object
uk.ac.manchester.cs.spinnaker.rest.utils.RestClientUtils
public abstract class RestClientUtils
extends Object
Manufactures clients for talking to other machines. This class does wicked things, but it is because users keep insisting on getting their security wrong. How difficult is it to just use LetsEncrypt? Apparently very because users instead stand up impossible-to-trust self-signed certificates! The infrastructure required to allow this to work securely requires a lot of interface changes (they'd have to supply the server's public certificate chain as part of the job submission) and that's just awkward.
